// checkVolChan — silent sound objects rewrite
// Original: -gr.checkVolChan (1994, French notes via -ho.Frenchnotes)
// Interactive controls (-in.abc1) not available → _script(Wait for g) kept as-is
// _chan/_vol/_cresc/_decresc/_switchon/_switchoff/_mod/_press/_presstep → _script(CTn)
// Only rules S and T tested (Init references external MIDI program)

RND
GRAM#1[1] T --> _script(CT0) mi5 sol4 fa4 mi4 re4 do4 re4 mi4 fa4 --------------------------------------- _script(CT1)
GRAM#1[2] S --> Init {Part1 Part2} _script(Wait for g) {Part3} {_script(CT7) Part2,_script(CT8) Part3} _script(MIDI all notes off channel 2)
GRAM#1[3] Part1 --> _script(CT2) _script(CT3) do4 re4 mi4 fa4 sol4 fa4 mi4 re4 do4 re4 mi4 fa4 _script(CT4)
GRAM#1[4] Part2 --> do4 _script(CT5) mi4 re4 fa4
GRAM#1[5] Part3 --> _script(CT6) sol4 si4 do5
GRAM#1[6] Init --> _script(MIDI program 0 channel 1) _script(MIDI controller #98 = 1 channel 1) - - -

// controlTable:
// CT0 = {switchon: "64,1"}
// CT1 = {switchoff: "64,1"}
// CT2 = {chan: 1, vol: 5}
// CT3 = {cresc: 1}
// CT4 = {vol: 127}
// CT5 = {vol: 30}
// CT6 = {chan: 4}
// CT7 = {chan: 2}
// CT8 = {vol: 54}
